  Palette: primary #2947C4 (riso federal blue), accent #F0426E (fluoro coral), bg #F2ECDC (newsprint), ink #181616, muted #8A8270.
  Fonts:   'Bricolage Grotesque' (display) + 'DM Sans' (body); 'DM Mono' for tabular figures.
  Anti-sameness: checked against the last 7 entries (Claymorphism, mid-century editorial, quiet-minimalism, art-deco banknote, bento security console, swiss-modernist flat, cinematic dark glassmorphism). The (risograph / riso blue+coral on newsprint / Bricolage+DM Sans) tuple collides with none of them.

STEP 4 — IMAGES
  Rationale: Risograph rewards bold halftone illustration, so the budget went to a hero pigeon + a 3-photo demo profile gallery (Bartholomew: head-on portrait, on-the-ledge, mid-strut). Testimonial headshots skipped intentionally so the coral accent stays rationed; the three named pigeons keep the two-ink monogram treatment.
